    "attributes": {
        "action": "Break the Brexit deadlock, change the way MPs vote",
        "additional_details": "All MP\u2019s can vote on as many options that they wish to support\r\nThe option with the most votes will be classed as Parliaments choice (does not need to be a majority)\r\nThis option will be given back to the people for a confirmation vote\r\nIn the event of a draw the two winning options will be run against each other\r\nIn this method the Brexit deadlock could be resolved swiftly, and subject to a peoples confirmation vote the country and Parliament would know which direction to work towards.",
        "background": "The Brexit deadlock could be easily resolved if they changed the way MP\u2019s voted on the Brexit options.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n\u2022\tPM\u2019s Deal \t\t\t\t\t        \uf064\r\n\u2022\tNo Deal (WTO) \t\t\t\t\t\uf064\r\n\u2022\tRevoke Article 50\t\t\t\t        \uf064\r\n\u2022\tCustoms union\t\t\t\t\t\uf064\r\n\u2022\tSingle market membership\t\t\t\uf064\r\n\u2022\tCommon Market 2.0\t\t\t\t\uf064",
